From 3918eaa369809580cf9bf58d67912879d198c36e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Guillem Jover <guillem@hadrons.org>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 05:44:16 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] doc: Avoid «allows …» which tends to be used incorrectly and
 unnecessarily
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The construct «allows to» is not grammatically correct, instead something
like «allows one to» should be used, but that is rather cumbersome, when
in many cases the surrounding text can be reworded to remove this entire
construct.

Origin: vendor
Forwarded: no
---
 README                | 6 +++---
 lib/physmem-windows.c | 2 +-
 lspci.man             | 2 +-
 pcilmr.man            | 2 +-
 setpci.man            | 2 +-
 5 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/README b/README
index f06cdbd..333dfc0 100644
--- a/README
+++ b/README
@@ -43,9 +43,9 @@ The utilities include:  (See manual pages for more details)
 
   - lspci: displays detailed information about all PCI buses and devices.
 
-  - setpci: allows to read from and write to PCI device configuration
-    registers. For example, you can adjust the latency timers with it.
-    CAUTION: There is a couple of dangerous points and caveats, please read
+  - setpci: read from and write to PCI device configuration registers.
+    For example, you can adjust the latency timers with it.
+    CAUTION: There are a couple of dangerous points and caveats, please read
     the manual page first!
 
   - update-pciids: download the current version of the pci.ids file.
diff --git a/lib/physmem-windows.c b/lib/physmem-windows.c
index 90f49e3..3f3d85e 100644
--- a/lib/physmem-windows.c
+++ b/lib/physmem-windows.c
@@ -860,7 +860,7 @@ physmem_map(struct physmem *physmem, u64 addr, size_t length, int w)
       /*
        * Note: Do not use WinAPI function MapViewOfFile() because it makes memory
        * mapping available also for all child processes that are spawned in the
-       * future. NtMapViewOfSection() allows to specify ViewUnmap parameter which
+       * future. NtMapViewOfSection() can be used to specify ViewUnmap parameter which
        * creates mapping just for this process and not for future child processes.
        * For security reasons we do not want this physical address mapping to be
        * present also in future spawned processes.
diff --git a/lspci.man b/lspci.man
index 938fac8..6b01b2c 100644
--- a/lspci.man
+++ b/lspci.man
@@ -198,7 +198,7 @@ available methods and their descriptions.
 .TP
 .B -O <param>=<value>
 The behavior of the library is controlled by several named parameters.
-This option allows one to set the value of any of the parameters. Use \fB-O help\fP
+This option sets the value of any of the parameters. Use \fB-O help\fP
 for a list of known parameters and their default values.
 .TP
 .B -H1
diff --git a/pcilmr.man b/pcilmr.man
index b2f3161..488ce83 100644
--- a/pcilmr.man
+++ b/pcilmr.man
@@ -59,7 +59,7 @@ the current Receiver position. Margining support for timing is required, while s
 for voltage is optional at 16.0 GT/s and required at 32.0 GT/s and higher data rates. Also,
 independent time margining and independent voltage margining is optional.
 
-Utility allows to get an approximation of the eye margin diagram in the form of a rhombus
+Utility to get an approximation of the eye margin diagram in the form of a rhombus
 (by four points). Lane Margining at the Receiver capability enables users to margin PCIe
 links without a hardware debugger and without the need to stop the target system. Utility
 can be useful to debug link issues due to receiver margins.
diff --git a/setpci.man b/setpci.man
index 1ec89da..5707c54 100644
--- a/setpci.man
+++ b/setpci.man
@@ -78,7 +78,7 @@ available methods and their descriptions.
 .TP
 .B -O <param>=<value>
 The behavior of the library is controlled by several named parameters.
-This option allows one to set the value of any of the parameters. Use \fB-O help\fP
+This option sets the value of any of the parameters. Use \fB-O help\fP
 for a list of known parameters and their default values.
 .TP
 .B -H1
-- 
